title: Live: Supergirls strike trouble early
text:
Bathurst 1000: Live coverage of V8 Supercars Race 25 from Mount Panorama Will Dale & Matthew Taylor FOX SPORTS Bathurst 1000: Live coverage of V8 Supercars Race 25 from Mount Panorama Will Dale & Matthew Taylor FOX SPORTS Bathurst Top 10 Shootout Highlights 1:47 
V8S: Check out the highlights from the Bathurst 1000 Top 10 Shootout laps. October 10th 2015 18 hours ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/Motor Sport/V8/ 
THE Harvey Norman Supergirls have been the first to strike trouble in the 2015 Bathurst 1000, Renee Gracie crashing on Lap 15. 
The V8 rookie was a passenger when she hit a trail of oil at Forrest’s Elbow, left by the expiring engine of David Wall’s Volvo. 
The team are looking to get the car repaired and back out on track to give Gracie and superstar import Simona de Silvestro a chance to gain experience around Mount Panorama. 
Scroll down below the blow for our report from this morning’s Warm Up session.
